Air mattresses are a home essential. Whether you need one for guests, traveling, camping or as a temporary place to sleep while you wait for your furniture delivery in a move — investing in a good quality air mattress is not one you’ll regret making. With so many options on the market, ranging in quality and price, it’s hard to know how much you need to spend to get a good nights sleep. So in an effort to make your shopping experience more enjoyable we surfed the net to do the groundwork for you. Ahead find six great air mattress options with thousands of raving Amazon reviews. Brands include Intex, King Koil, EnerPlex and more. The Intex Dura-Beam Deluxe Comfort Plus Air Mattress is not only an “Amazon’s Choice” product but it has earned a 4.4-star rating with more than 20,000 reviews. It comes in a variety of heights, three sizes (twin, full and queen) and for just $65 — you can’t beat the price! The King Koil air mattress is another great option with even more reviews. It comes with a built in pump and is available in sizes as small as a twin and as large as a California king. Get the EnerPlex mattress in twin, queen or king size and enjoy it while camping, at-home or anywhere else you desire. Since it’s made with waterproof material, it’s uses are endless. Get The Englander air mattress in two different colors and three different sizes. This baby can blow up your bed in just 90 seconds and deflates itself with the push of a button. If you’re looking for a little more support and want a air mattress with a built-in headboard, consider this Intex model that has almost 5,000 reviews and is on sale for $154. If you and your family often take road trips, this car air mattress bed will be an item you use regularly. For just $33, give it a try! For more recommendations, check out the New York Post Shopping section.